==English==

===Etymology===
From {{bor|en|fr|accompagnement}}; equivalent to {{suffix|en|accompany|ment}}. First attested in 1744.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|ə-kŭmʹpə-nē-mənt}}, {{IPA|en|/ə.ˈkʌm.pə.ni.mənt/|/ə.ˈkʌmp.ni.mənt/}}
* {{audio|en|En-us-accompaniment.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{lb|en|music}} A [[part]], usually performed by instruments, that gives [[support]] or adds to the background in music, or adds for [[ornamentation]]; also, the [[harmony]] of a [[figured bass]].
#: {{ux|en|Brooks performed a saxophone solo on stage, with Robert as '''accompaniment''' on the bass.}}
# That which [[accompany|accompanies]]; something that attends as a [[circumstance]], or which is added to give greater completeness to the principal thing, or by way of [[ornament]], or for the sake of [[symmetry]].
#: {{syn|en|attachment|supplement|Thesaurus:adjunct}}
#: {{ux|en|A side salad is a common '''accompaniment''' to a main dish.}}

